==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fieri facias
<hw>Fi"e*ri fa"ci*as</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L., cause it to be
done.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A judicial writ that lies for one who
has recovered in debt or damages, commanding the sheriff that he cause
to be made of the goods, chattels, or real estate of the defendant, the
sum claimed.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone. Cowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fieriness</ent>⟦br⟧
